<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Dikmer on 03-21-2001 06:03 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by Darianne:
[b]We were talking about spell drops, so I'll concentrate mainly on the 3 wis casters, and 4 int casters... only the cleric has to worry about travel, and any annoyances that go along with it.[/b][/QUOTE]

Ok, you lost me here. Shaman and Druids being the other 2 of the 3 wis casters. Both get Spirit of the Wolf, Druids get Teleport. Now, of the 4 int casters, only the Wizard gets ports, or am I way off base here? I simply don't remember reading anywhere that Chanters, Necros and Mages get any kind of "travel" spell. I think those 3 classes are in the same boat as us when it comes to travel. Either hoof it, or seek a port from someone else.

 [QUOTE][b]So we also really need to bring up the med-heal routine? I dunno about you guys but I try and break the routine as much as I can... but it can still be a pain... every class mentioned there, gets SOME form of mana regen but the cleric (yes, some of them are very tiny).[/b][/QUOTE]

You lost me here too. Wizards get a mana regen? Which spell is it? Druids get one too?   To my knowledge, which is admittedly 8 months out of date, only 4 of the 7 classes you listed get any form of mana-regen. Necros, with leech, Enchanters, with breeze/clarity/etc, Mages with those Mod Rods, and Shamans, with Cannabalize. And do mage really count, since they can't heal the damage they take from the rod, plus it costs mana to summon the rod? A Shaman can regen/heal himself, a Necro can Lifetap his life back, and an Enchanter doesn't need to.

  [QUOTE][b]I think you said we were pampered due to not having to research spells and only have a few droppable spells... well that applies to druids and shamans too... except some of the shaman spells are more useful that are dropped.  Int casters have to research spells... I played one, it can be a pain (especially for mages having to get all that crap, and necros who have way too many research only spells)... but at the same time, an INT casters has a WAY easier time reaching 200 int than we do 200 wis... and for them AC is not so much of a concern.[/b][/QUOTE]

I am an average dwarf (started with 100 base wis) with (mainly) average gear. And I have 180 wis. I could get 200 with some sacrifice of AC, but I ain't willing to do that. I am more willing to wait til I get EM legs and BP or equivelent. I do just fine with my 180wis, and still get compliments on the way I play. It aint about the size your manapool, but how you use it.

  [QUOTE][b]I'm envious of other classes travel ability more than anything else... but I like what I'm doing now, I have no desire to be one of them.[/b][/QUOTE]

There it is. Enough said.

